m/xBq4BVn.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/lqKGjkF</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DamnitCheryl]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Wish us a good journey.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/oZD5RwI</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lmTjLxP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Evgeniya Parishkura who left Odesa Ukraine yesterday with family and three cats Ajax, Agatha, Martha safely cross Romanian border:

https://imgur.com/gallery/Wn3iy4L</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/c8WfggU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/oZD5RwI</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[aaaaaaaa0]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Improvised body armor for Ukrainians</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/hlUy6g6</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/QBxNrEf.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Today I’m going to be providing an instructional video for the construction of improvised bullet resistant plates as well as some of my own findings from testing plates constructed using this method, something I think our friends in Ukraine could use going forward. 

Required materials:

1. Epoxy resin
2. Fiberglass welding blankets
3. Several C-clamps (preferably metal) 
4. A respirator of sufficient quality for working with fiberglass 
5. A jig saw
6. Two dummy plates, made of wood or preferably metal, shaped as you want the finished product to be shaped
7. Packing tape (It helps to keep your final plate from getting stuck to the dummy plates) 

Link to video: 
https://youtu.be/_7jiIQOgwtI

My personal findings: 

Through some of my own testing after making these plates I can corroborate the following results of the video

The plates produced through this method of construction without fail stopped bullets of the following calibers at close range (10 yards): 

9x19mm 125 grain FMJ fired from a glock 17
.45 acp 230 grain FMJ fired from a glock 21
.40 S&W 180 grain FMJ fired from a glock 23
.380 auto 92 grain FMJ fired from a S&W bodyguard
12 gauge 000 buckshot fired from a Remington 870
12 gauge rifled slugs fired from a Remington 870

I can also corroborate that this armor will not stop 5.56 or 7.62 at close range, however at 300 yards or more, it will consistently stop the following cartridges

5.56x45mm NATO 62 grain FMJ-BT fired from a civilian AR-15 with 16 inch barrel (a decent approximation of the Russian 5.45x39mm cartridge) 

7.62x39mm 122 grain FMJ fired from a civilian AK-47 with 16.5 inch barrel 

Wear your goddam respirator while making these things 

Slava Ukraini</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/hlUy6g6</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[T3NM1DG3TS]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>meet Brucie</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/t6chKNz</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lb8IC1Z.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/t6chKNz</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[joey69420]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>President zelensklyy with his family. this is a man who knows what he's fighting for.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/uzJ7Ptv</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lbee7GZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/uzJ7Ptv</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ste1LionSlosh69]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/aNt3LdZ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/EslJVfG.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/aNt3LdZ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Noonius]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Like that’s going to work</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/X63bYm4</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1JqVyrv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/X63bYm4</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[NotAGazelle]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>When you have your priorities in order</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Lo70GAT</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Ilgg1Tt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Lo70GAT</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[LogicDude]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Please tread on me</title><link>h